history.content:
I'm a CS Senior graduating next Fall.


CS184 waitlist currently at 127 students for the class that has max size of 130 students, and the class is already 70% filled. I am position 124.



My questions are:


- Are there any chances of this class getting expanded? I looked through every previous semester and there weren't nearly as many students enrolled or on the waitlist at this point in the enrollment timeline. 


- If it is not expanded, should I expect to not get into the class at all? It's a pretty intense class to stick around for a couple weeks and drop later because of not being able to add.


- Will it be offered in Fall 2018? That is my last semester and I saw that it is not generally offered during the fall (for example this one it was not) and I'm wondering if i will be able to take it before I graduate.
history.subject: CS184: waitlist, petition for expansion, offering in the spring
